  "text": "Alternatively, a variety of rapid prototyping technologies have been explored for fabricating 3-D microwave circuits and EBG components, including polymer and ceramic stereolithography [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , fused deposition modeling [CITATION_3] and selective laser sintering [CITATION_4] . Among them, polymer stereolithography has the highest accuracy [CITATION_5] . Using these methods, EBG waveguides [CITATION_6] , 3-D antennas [17] and band-pass filters [CITATION_7] have been demonstrated. However, these techniques were only successful at frequencies up to approximately 30 GHz.",
